IntegratedAnalysis<N,E,T,G,CombinedIntegratedAnalysis.CombinedAssumption>
public class CombinedIntegratedAnalysis<N,E,T,G extends Graph<N,E,T>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements IntegratedAnalysis<N,E,T,G,CombinedIntegratedAnalysis.CombinedAssumption>

Integrated analysis, which combines several other integrated analyses into one. It does so be defining combined assumption, which is vector of original assumptions, and applies each analysis to its own component. If any analysis decides to rewrite the node, combined analysis returns produced transformation. If more than one analyses decide to transform, the first one wins.
